38 company act, and whose compensation is not based on the volume
39 of premiums written.
40 4. The manager of a group, association, pool, or
41 organization of insurers which engage in joint underwriting or
42 joint reinsurance and who are subject to examination by the
43 insurance regulatory authority of the state in which the
44 manager's principal business office is located.
45 5. An underwriting manager which manages assumed
46 facultative risks for a reinsurer if the facultative reinsurance
47 business managed by the underwriting manager is less than 10
48 percent of the assumed annual gross written premium of the
49 reinsurer.
